<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Fake Token Price Display</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            max-width: 800px;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            line-height: 1.6;
        }
        .price-display {
            font-size: 48px;
            color: #28a745;
            margin: 20px 0;
        }
        .warning {
            background-color: #f8d7da;
            color: #721c24;
            padding: 15px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            margin: 20px 0;
            border: 1px solid #f5c6cb;
        }
        .section {
            margin: 30px 0;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ddd;
            border-radius: 5px;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Fake Token Price Display Simulation</h1>
    <p>This interface demonstrates how scam tokens can display fake prices to deceive users.</p>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Current Price Display</h2>
        <div class="price-display">FAKE-USDT: $1.00</div>
        <p>Last updated: <span id="timestamp"></span></p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="warning">
        <strong>WARNING: This is a demonstration only.</strong><br>
        Real market price in liquidity pool: $0.003
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Scam Mechanism</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Fake API returns constant $1.00 price</li>
            <li>Wallet displays the fake price to user</li>
            <li>Users purchase token thinking it's stable</li>
            <li>Scammers execute rug pull (drain liquidity)</li>
            <li>Price crashes to near zero</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
    
    <div class="section">
        <h2>Detection Methods</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Check multiple price sources (CoinGecko, CoinMarketCap, DEX)</li>
            <li>Verify liquidity pool depth and volume</li>
            <li>Analyze contract code for malicious functions</li>
            <li>Use trusted oracle services</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
    
    <script>
        function updateTimestamp() {
            const now = new Date();
            document.getElementById('timestamp').textContent = 
                now.toLocaleString('en-US', { 
                    year: 'numeric', 
                    month: 'short', 
                    day: 'numeric',
                    hour: '2-digit',
                    minute: '2-digit',
                    second: '2-digit'
                });
        }
        
        updateTimestamp();
        setInterval(updateTimestamp, 5000);
    </script>
</body>
</html>
